---

LICENSE FEE

All use of the Protocol under versions prior to v1.0.0 (including all alpha
and beta releases) is free of charge. No license fee applies and no
reporting or registration is required during this period.

Upon the release of v1.0.0, the following terms apply:

The first 100 billable artifacts (CONTRIBUTION_RESULTs and
POH_CERTIFICATEs combined) issued by an operator are free of
charge, counted in aggregate across all Referee nodes operated by the
same person or organization. No reporting or registration is required
below this threshold.

This threshold is bound to the operator, not to the Referee node
identifier. Issuing a new referee_id does not reset the count.

Once an operator has issued 100 or more billable artifacts
(CONTRIBUTION_RESULTs and POH_CERTIFICATEs combined) in total
across all of its Referee nodes, the following terms apply:

  - A license fee of USD 1.00 per CONTRIBUTION_RESULT and USD 1.00 per
    POH_CERTIFICATE applies to all such artifacts from the 101st onward,
    regardless of whether a FEE_DEPOSIT was recorded for that artifact.
  - The operator_contact field MUST be populated with accurate contact
    information in the REFEREE_PROFILE of every Referee node the
    operator runs.
  - Operators who wish to continue operating beyond 100 assessments without
    a license fee (e.g., academic research, registered non-profit use) must
    submit an exemption request to RACKP before exceeding the threshold.
    Exemptions are granted at RACKP's discretion.

License accounting is based on operator self-reporting. ASSESSMENT_ISSUED
and POH_CERT_ISSUED anchors recorded in Keepers provide an independently
auditable record against which self-reported counts are reconciled:
anchored artifacts establish a verifiable lower bound, so a self-report
falling short of the publicly anchored record is evidence of
under-reporting. The obligation to report accurately binds the operator
regardless of what is externally observable.

Fee schedules may be revised independently of the Protocol specification.
The current fee schedule is maintained at:
  https://github.com/rackp-io/rackp

To inquire about licensing or exemptions:
  https://github.com/rackp-io/rackp/issues

Report submissions contain operator business information and are not
accepted through the public issue tracker. A dedicated reporting
channel is being finalized and will be announced in this repository
no later than the release of v1.0.0.

RACKP may publish the Referee ID, endpoint, and issued-artifact count of
operators who have exceeded the 100-artifact threshold and have not
registered an operator_contact or responded to payment inquiries within
30 days of notification.

Anchoring (CLAIM_ANCHOR records sent to a Keeper) carries no license fee.
Keeper node operation carries no license fee payable to RACKP. Keeper
operators may charge their own fees to Actors, Claimants, and Referees
for their services under separate commercial arrangements.
Referee operators may likewise charge their own fees to Actors and
Claimants for assessment services, independent of the per-artifact
license fee payable to RACKP.

---

PRIVATE AND OFFLINE USE

Deployments not accessible to parties outside the operator's own
organization — including on-premises, VPN, and air-gapped environments —
are exempt from the per-artifact license fee, regardless of
issued-artifact count.

Operators requiring formal licensing certification for enterprise or
procurement purposes may contact RACKP with their Referee's terminal_id:
  https://github.com/rackp-io/rackp/issues

